description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NMC Registered Nurse Associate&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Band 4&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An extremely exciting opportunity is available to recruit a new Registered Nursing Associates to our existing workforce. The Walton Centre NHS Foundation Trust is the only NHS Trust in the UK dedicated to Neurosciences treating a range of conditions affecting the brain and spine.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be passionate, dedicated and innovative in order to help maintain a dynamic service whilst adhering to the Walton Way values.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be responsible for monitoring the condition and health needs of people within their care on a continual basis in partnership with Registered Nurses and the multi professional team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Through the principles of care will;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• promote and monitor safe and effective nursing practice&lt;br /&gt;• enhance the patient experience&lt;br /&gt;• contribute to the delivery of the organisation’s objectives&lt;br /&gt;You will;&lt;br /&gt;• Work within the Nursing Associate parameters of practice &lt;br /&gt;• Work within the organisational policy, standard operating procedures and guidelines&lt;br /&gt;• Be responsible and accountable for own practice, working within limits of competence and within professional boundaries&lt;br /&gt;• Raise any concerns to a registered care professional or appropriate person&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will promote a caring environment where equality and diversity issues are respected and patients and their carers are enabled to be partners in their care. &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt;You will have attained a level 5 foundation degree as well as NMC registration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details or informal inquiries contact Sarah.Flynn@thewaltoncentre.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
